               <msContents>
                  <summary>Images 5r-173r: Psalter. The midpoint of the Psalms is unmarked. Psalm 151 is the short version. The fourth biblical canticle has the standard superscription. The Song of Songs in in the common version. The Praises of Mary begins with Monday and culminates on Sunday. Image 1r: a few illegible words, in pencil and in ink pen. Illuminations added recently over text.  Image 173l, col. 2: Record of sale of book, including the names of buyer, seller, witnesses. The names are Tigrinian. It also mentions King ኃይለ ሥላሴ, and the "year of Luke, ፳፫ ዓመተ ምሕረት, የጌና ቀን, i.e., on Christmas day.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <textLang/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
